<TITLE> Govt buying Jeeps for UZ chairmen </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 11 (bdnews24.com)The government will purchase new Jeeps for the Upazila chairmen to help them serve people fast, the finance minister said on Monday The vehicles, each at Tk 37 lakh, will cost over Tk 160 crore, Abdul Mal Abul Muhith told bdnews24.com in the evening. The purchase committee of the ministry is likely to approve of the proposal. The budget for FY 2009-10 will allocate fund for the purchase, said Muhith. He defended the spending on transport at a time when the government was encouraging cost savings. "It is necessary for the public representatives to perform." Sources close to the Cabinet Division said early on April 1, government transport directorate invited tender for purchasing 471 Jeeps for as many upazila chairmen. After reviewing the biddings, the committee at its Tuesday' meeting decided the bidder that quoted the lowest price to supply the vehicles. The elections to the local government body were held on Jan 22 and 471 of the 481 Upazila chairmen have taken oath since bd
